column3: De Bordeaux is a very quiet street with little traffic, and free parking is usually quite easy to find. It is a residential neighborhood, with many young families and cute alleys  full of lurking cats. There is a very well stocked dépanneur (corner store) very close by (1 minute) where basic groceries, a few gourmet products, some vegan milks and a great selection of microbrewed beers are available. It is right next to a cute bakery. There is a pharmacy nearby, and some grocery stores 5 or 10 minutes away by foot. Montreal's iconic Plateau is just on the other side of the train tracks (don't worry—we can't hear the trains from the apartment). Along the track runs a great cycle path that is safe from traffic and wide enough to accommodate walkers, runners and bikers. It runs all the way to the metro station (Rosemont), about ten minutes by bixi or twenty by foot.

column3: “A ilha do Porto" is a working-class neighborhood, very different from that of other industrial cities, which first appeared in the eastern part of the city of Porto (Campanhã) in the late 19th century, with the arrival of many migrants from the northern lands from the country The bourgeois houses were built at one end of the land, and the proprietor opened a link through a narrow corridor to the back of the yard with a street connection, along which he built small, precarious housing to house whole families. The Oporto living house is one of those old bourgeois houses, totally restored and where you can see “as ilhas" as living quarters, contrary to the cold and impersonal spirit that increasingly defines the current life In Porto, more than a thousand of these neighborhoods ("ilhas") are scattered throughout the city.

column3: 旺角位于九龙半岛的北部,著名的弥敦道贯穿其中,这里是香港人气最旺盛的地区之一,潮流时尚､传统文化､市井风貌､小吃美食都汇集于此,全区繁华拥挤,不少商铺食肆通宵营业,故被称为是九龙的“不夜天”｡ 购物指南 旺角或许没有尖沙咀那样鳞次栉比的国际大牌专卖店,但却是不少年轻人心中的购物圣地｡这里购物场所各有特色,大型商场朗豪坊聚集了大量潮流时装､创意杂货店;妹子们最爱的化妆品店SASA､卓悦都有多家分店;西洋菜南街附近丰泽､苏宁､百脑汇等电子数码店一家挨着一家;田园书屋､序言书室等知名楼上书店也都安家旺角;日韩潮流和二次元文化爱好者不能错过的圣地信和中心;运动鞋一条街波鞋街不仅可以享受折扣价,还能买到各大品牌的海外限定款;还有可以边淘价廉物美的杂货,边感受老香港市井风情的传统购物街女人街､花园街等等｡ 美食推荐 旺角整区都布满了特色的美食店,有东南亚美食､日本菜､甜品店､茶餐厅等｡此外,旺角也以小吃店繁多出名,有很多潮流小吃店也是以旺角为根据地,其中包括日式烧饼､德国肉肠､台式饮品等｡推荐几家人气较高餐厅:稻香､翠华餐厅､肥姐小食店､池记､发记甜品､佳记小食､金华冰厅､沙嗲王､富记粥品､妹记生滚粥品｡ 【特别提示】 1. 逛旺角建议选择平底舒适的鞋子,避免高跟鞋｡ 2. 商铺上午通常开门较晚,可避免一大早前往购物｡ 3. 特色街上人很多,逛街时候还需注意安全｡

column3: You couldn't be better located. The apartment is located in Eixample, the most iconic neighbourhood in the centre of Barcelona. You will be located in an charming area with the best of Barcelona’s modernism alongside elegant shops and boutiques. Main landmarks include Gaudi’s awe-inspiring Sagrada Familia and Plaza Catalunya, where shopaholics will find an array of commercial chains and boutiques offering all the latest trends.  You’ll have plenty of opportunities to try some typical Spanish and Catalonian gastronomy in the restaurants which populate the area. They include the revered Teoric Taverna Gastronomica, where gleaming reviews are proof of the high quality Mediterranean dishes on offer and Don Kilo Barcelona, an extremely popular restaurant serving Italian classics.  This neighbourhood is well-connected to the main city attractions and offers great public transport connections, so enjoy the area knowing that other exciting Barcelona neighbourhoods are within easy reach!

column3: A Lapa é um bairro de boêmio da Zona Central do município do Rio de Janeiro, no Brasil. Possui uma grande variedade de bares, restaurantes, boates e pubs temáticos, que atendem a todos os gostos ao longo de suas treze ruas. Sendo conhecido como o berço da boemia carioca, na atual efervescência do bairro, quinze novos estabelecimentos foram abertos em 2018. Também é famosa pela arquitetura, a começar pelo Aqueduto da Carioca, sua principal referência e cartão-postal, que foi construído para funcionar como aqueduto nos tempos do Brasil Colonial e que, desde 1896, serve como via para o bonde que liga o Centro ao bairro de Santa Teresa.

column3: Laranjeiras é um dos bairros mais antigos da cidade, e é onde estão situados o  Palácio Guanabara, sede do Governo do Estado do Rio de Janeiro, o Palácio Laranjeiras, residência oficial do Governador do Estado do Rio de Janeiro, o Parque Guinle e o Fluminense Football Club. Bairro tipicamente residencial, de classe média alta e classe alta, tem a Rua das Laranjeiras como a sua principal via, a qual começa no Largo do Machado e termina nas imediações do Túnel Rebouças, já com outro nome: Rua Cosme Velho. Ao contrário do que se pensa, o nome do bairro não vem da existência de grandes laranjais na parte baixa do vale do Rio Carioca e sim da sua semelhança com a acidentada região de Laranjeiras na região mais alta de Lisboa, o que levou à nomeação do bairro carioca. Laranjeiras ainda guarda o charme dos bairros marcados pelo passado e foi o endereço de nobres, escritores, compositores e pessoas ilustres, como Villa-Lobos, Cecília Meirelles, Portinari, Oscar Niemeyer e Cássia Eller

column3: Experience the feeling of living in a house on wheels and visit Portugal from top to bottom. Stop wherever you want to, whenever you want, make your meals and sleep when and where you feel like. The choice is always yours! You can have your breakfast by the sea, wake up in the middle of the mountains, have dinner outside with a view over the city, and fall asleep under the starry sky. The choice is yours! You can be in contact with nature, in the company of friends, family and your pets. It is simple and uncomplicated. You don’t have to book hotels, there are no arrival schedules to limit you, no prepaid programs to follow. It is about total freedom of choice and use. Start your journey and discover and enjoy the unique adventure that is Portugal!

column3: Eixample is a beautiful area of the city which includes some of the most popular attractions and iconic monuments in Barcelona. This district lies in the center of Barcelona, above Ciutat Vella and below the district of Gràcia. Running through the heart of Eixample is the famed Passeig de Gràcia, a long thoroughfare that houses some of Barcelona’s most exclusive shopping and is home to some of Gaudí’s most famous works like Casa Batlló and Casa Milà. At the end, you will come to Plaça Catalunya, one of the most visited places in Barcelona. Another monument that should not be missed in Eixample is La Sagrada Família, possibly the most recognized building in Barcelona and an icon of the city. With so much to see and do, no wonder Eixample is so popular!

column3: The Eixample district of Barcelona in the 19th century is the birthplace of the Modernist movement, of which Antoni Gaudi is considered the leader. If you are looking to experience the world-renowned reputation of Barcelona for leading the architecture of the 19th century, this area is magnificent. With all the monuments of Gaudi within reach, such as the impressive Sagrada Familia, the two famous houses of Gaudi: La Pedrera and the Apple of Discord; the Hospital of Santa Creu i Sant Pau in expansion, you will be able to spend hours walking and contemplating it. This area decorated with grilles was created in the nineteenth century to accommodate the growing population of the old Barcelona; fortunately, this coincided with the golden age of Barcelona's architecture ... Gaudí, Puig i Cadafalch, Domènech i Montaner were hired by the rich to build houses, each time more daring ... The Eixample district is divided in two, the Eixample Dreta (right side) and the Eixample Esquerra (left side

column3: Tucked away behind the hustle and bustle of Causeway Bay, the Tai Hang neighborhood offers a laid-back alternative to all the buzz. Slow-paced yet rapidly evolving, the enclave is home to a wellspring of restaurants, vintage stores, artisanal coffee shops, and a growing lineup of design-driven boutiques.  A wander around the neighborhood will take you past the 19th-century Lin Fa Temple, sporting graceful eaves and a unique octagonal front hall. It’s here where the annual Fire Dragon Dance takes place during Mid-Autumn Festival, usually in September. A centuries-old ritual, the traditional dance features some 300 performers with incense sticks and firecrackers—believed to extinguish bad luck. Behind the temple, Lin Fa Kung Garden provides a peaceful resting spot. Nearby Victoria Park, just a few minutes’ walk northwest, offers jogging paths, tennis courts, shady corners, and Tai Chi sessions every morning.

column3: El Raval is a  neighbourhood in the Ciutat Vella district of Barcelona, Spain. The area, especially the part closest to the port, was also informally known as Barri Xinès or Barrio Chino, meaning "Chinatown". El Raval is one of the two historical neighborhoods that border La Rambla, the other being the Barri Gòtic, and contains some 50,000 people. An area historically infamous for its nightlife and cabarets, as well as prostitution and crime, El Raval has changed significantly in recent years and due to its central location has become a minor attraction of Barcelona. It is home to many bars, restaurants, and night spots.

Stop at the Basilique Notre-Dame to admire its splendid stain-glass window (and for a moment of peace and quiet). Then head off to the historic Place Jacques-Cartier and settle down at one of its terraces, where you’ll get a great view street artists and portrait painters and where the sangria flows like water. - The Little-Italy, which is more steeped in tradition. You’ll always feel warmly welcomed. And the Jean-Talon market, one of the gems of the city, making it one of the city’s most valued areas. - The Village, a neighbourhood where you’ll never be bored. Constantly lively and festive, with more than enough atmosphere to spare.

column3: Popular amongst tourists and locals alike, Old Montreal’s history and charm are undeniable. The city’s iconic waterfront, known as the Old Port, is famous for its cobblestone streets, horse-drawn carriages, and effervescent Promenade. This vibrant area offers lots of sightseeing as well as year round activities for all ages, such as bike and boat rentals in the summer, and ice skating in the winter. Old Montreal is also rich in upscale restaurants like Club Chasse et Pêche and L’Auberge Saint Gabriel, or take advantage of the great nightlife options at places like Velvet nightclub or the trendy Terrasses Bonsecours. There are also plenty of services in proximity, and with the Champ-de-Mars metro station nearby, the downtown core is never far away. So if you’re planning your next stay in Montreal and want the best the city has to offer, Old Montreal will not disappoint!

Coogee is a bustling beach with an abundance of restaurants, cafes and the newly opened Coogee Pavillion. Just around the corner from us is an excellent Thai takeaway, sushi bar, coffee house and famous fish and chip shop. A bistro, deli and bakery complete our very local area as well as the Clovelly Hotel (pub). We are 1 minute from Gordons Bay, with an amazing underwater snorkelling trail, calm water and an interesting rocky shoreline, perfect for sunbaking and lagoon-style swimming.

column3: The East Village (EV) is known for its cool bars and nightlife, great restaurants, and music venues. It is very hipster, artsy and unique. My block, specifically, is a living reminder of the East Village's punk-rock past. Significant moments in counterculture history happened all along the street: Abbie Hoffman invented the Yippies at No. 30 in 1967; Andy Warhol, the Velvet Underground, and Jimi Hendrix performed at now-gone experimental nightclub Electric Circus, before it closed in 1971; and gallery 51X backed eighties-era graffiti artists like Keith Haring and Basquiat. Today, the street's grasp on culture lies mostly within its diverse restaurants (frankfurters at Crif Dogs, Israeli cuisine at Hummus Place) and storefronts. And though these aren’t quite as anti-establishment as they once were—there’s nothing too rebellious about sidewalk vendors hawking plastic sunglasses—some glam stalwarts still remain, like Trash & Vaudeville and Andy's Chee-Pees, where you can still sift throug

column3: Located in the modernist Eixample district, this apartment is in one of the most fascinating areas of Barcelona. Less than five minutes from your front door you come to Passeig De Gracia. Littered with designer shops, bars and restaurants, this is home to three stunning examples of the modernist movement, La Pedrera, Casa Battlo and Casa Amatller. Take a walk in the other direction from your apartment down the Passeig De Sant Joan and it will bring you into Barcelona’s Arc de Triomf, this will lead you onto a beautiful boulevard that takes you to the Parc Ciutadella, which houses the Zoo, the botanical gardens and many more attractions. If that is not enough for you, the metro stops Girona and Passeig de Gracia are only five minutes away from your front door and take you to the heart of the centre in less than ten minutes. All in all, a perfect place for you to enjoy this great city.

column3: Der Küste der Copacabana ist 4,5 km lang, die Strandpromenade aus Stein ist ein Werk des Landschaftsarchitekten Burle Marx verziert mit Wellen wie vom Meer. Über das Seebad können Besucher die Promenade zu Fuß erreichen. Im Sommer ist es üblich, dass Menschen Nachts ein Bad im Meer genießen, weil die Hitze im Rio sehr stark ist und das Meer von Copacabana sich in einen Mondschein-Pool verwandelt. Die Aussicht ist oft erstaunlich!  In Copacabana gibt es auch zwei Festungen, die besichtigt werden können, die  befinden sich an einem Ende des Strandes. Eine von ihnen ist das Fort von Copacabana. In der Nacht bietet der Strand ein Höchstmaß an Spaß und Erholung, Kioske, Bars und Restaurants sind an der Küste und in den nahe gelegenen Alleen. Die Restaurants servieren die typischsten Getränke von Rio De Janeiro, wie Caipirinha, und auch weitere würzige Snacks.

column3: This is an amazing and totally safe neighbourhood, where old and new Hong Kong collide in beautiful ways. The area is the heart of hip Hong Kong.  International art galleries, restaurants and bars abound, Yet historic Hong Kong is everywhere. The apartment is built on the site where Sun Yat Sen planned China's revolution in 1898. Across the road is one if the city's most loved noodle shops (US$5 a bowl). Next door is one of HKs last outdoor cafes (Toast and condensed milk, US$2). Next street is Gage Street market, a photographers paradise. One street up is Hollywood Road and PMQ - the Art Heart. Then, there is Soho, Noho, Sheung Wan and Lan Kwai Fong all just five minutes stumble away.

column3: The Upper East Side has it all. There's the UES of Edith Wharton and Gossip Girl -- the grand museums of Museum Mile, elegant shops, Park Avenue promenades. column3: The Rambla Catalunya runs parallel to the chic Passeig de Gràcia and the busy Carrer Balmes. One either side of the boulevard, there are buildings with a plethora of modernista details. The Rambla grew up in the middle of the Eixample and was influenced by the elegance of the new Barcelona. It has always been a street crammed with shops, art galleries, theatres and cinemas, some of which have disappeared or been transformed with the passing of the years. In addition to two cinemas and traditional shops, you can find a wide retail offering in the form of leading fashion boutiques, destined to make a shopaholic's dreams come true. Select shops blend with more traditional outlets, tracing a shopping line that follows the layout of the street. Plaza Catalunya and the Ramblas are a 5-minute walk from the apartments.

column3: Within a few blocks of the apartment, you'll discover the many reasons that Williamsburg has become the global definition of "cool".  At the famous Nitehawk Cinema, you can watch movies while being served brunch. At local coffee shops, like Devocion, Toby's Estate, and Blue Bottle, you can hang out with more hipsters than probably where else in the world. The nightlife is probably Williamsburg's strongest feature, with several excellent cocktail bars nearby (I especially like Hotel Delmano and Maison Premiere), many options for live music, as well as the two best nightclubs in NYC (Verboten and Output). In summer, there's the outdoor foodie market Smorgasburg. There's excellent shopping at unique boutiques: escape the chain stores and global luxury labels that now dominate Manhattan.

column3: There's plenty to offer within walking distance. Try out P'tit Plateau or Arepera du Plateau for some of Montreal's best dining. For shopping, head to Place Ville Marie for your typical fashion stores. To explore the rest of the city, take the nearest metro at Mont-Royal Station. For an authentic Montreal experience, skip downtown and hang out with the locals in Le Plateau. Nestled at the foot of Mont Royal, Le Plateau is the epicenter of entertainment and culture in this diverse city. Day or night, the streets of Saint Denis, Mont Royal Ave, and Saint Laurent Boulevard come alive with residents and tourists alike. Eat your way through a variety of restaurants, and adventure through countless shops, cafés, and bars. Save some time to explore Saint Laurent Boulevard, where you'll find all sorts of unique urban art installations on every turn, thanks to the annual Montreal Mural Festival.

column3: Park Slope is a beautiful, landmark neighborhood, including tree lined streets, gourmet restaurants, easy access to transportation, and Prospect Park - the largest public park in Brooklyn. In 2010, New York Magazine selected Park Slope as the finest neighborhood in New York City, citing its overall safety, fine dining, eclectic nightlife, local shopping, and close proximity to public transit, green space, quality housing, and creative capital.  In 2007, Park Slope was named one of the "Greatest Neighborhoods in America" by the American Planning Association "for its architectural and historical features and its diverse mix of residents and businesses".  And in December 2006, Natural Home magazine named Park Slope one of America's ten best neighborhoods, citing area greenspaces, neighborhood gathering spaces, local farmer's markets, strong public transportation, and interesting locally owned businesses.

Se você olhar para o mar, o Leme estará à sua esquerda, no final da praia, depois da Av. Princesa Isabel. O Leme é o início da praia de Copacabana, e o bairro de Copa  é sem dúvida o bairro mais carioca do Rio de janeiro! Eu costumo dizer que moro onde a maioria das pessoas gostariam de passar férias! Copacabana, carinhosamente chamado de Copa pelos cariocas, é um bairro nobre situado na Zona Sul da cidade do Rio de Janeiro, no Brasil. É considerado por muitos um dos bairros mais famosos e prestigiados do Brasil e um dos mais conhecidos do mundo. Tem o apelido de Princesinha do Mar e Coração da Zona Sul. Faz divisa com os também bairros nobres da Lagoa, Ipanema, Botafogo e é contínuo ao Leme. column3: Molokai is one of the only Hawaiian islands where you can still experience the unspoiled natural beauty of Hawaii. Things move at a slower pace without a skyscraper or stoplight in sight. Many residents still practice traditional Hawaiian customs, including warm hospitality. The small town of Kaunakakai has everything you need with a large dose of small town charm. Head to Kanemitsu bakery for a tasty brunch or late at night in the back alley for their famous hot bread - the perfect late night sweet treat. Molokai Pizza Cafe and Molokai Burger serve up familiar foods as well as local specials. Pick up groceries and other essentials at Friendly Market or Misaki’s. Souvenir shop in all of the locally owned businesses in town. If you’d rather explore the great outdoors, Molokai has everything an adventurer needs. The island has beautiful hikes, pristine waterfalls, incredible views and spectacular beaches without the crowds. From the hot and sunny west side to the lush and green east side

column3: Maroubra is roughly 10km from the centre of Sydney, in the Eastern Suburbs. We have lived in the area for around 6 years, and we absolutely love it! It has a great community atmosphere and it's hard to walk down the street to the beach without running into people we know. We know and love lots of the cafe and restaurant owners in the area, and have made friends with lots of the neighbours.  The beach is the highlight of the area, and it's right across the street! Maroubra beach is 1km long and is popular for surfing, swimming, a BBQ, a nice spot to sit and have lunch/dinner or just a walk to get some fresh air, space and relax. It's less crowded than its neighbour up in Bondi, but no less beautiful. To the south end there is a reserve with no buildings or houses, so it's particularly beautiful looking down the sand and waves to the trees and headland. column3: It is a perfect getaway in the midst of the enchanting neighborhood of Cihangir, with restaurants and cafes just steps away. It  takes a short walk to reach Taksim, international center area of Istanbul. You can easily and quickly access some of the best  restaurants, cafes, shops, art scenes, and nightlife in the city! The apartment is very easy to find, as well as easily accessible  by all forms of public transportation – you can even reach Asian side in under half an hour via ferry.  Besides the option of walking around in this enchanting area, there are various methods of public transportation available around  the apartment. You can always take the tram from Tophane to get to the old part of Istanbul, or take the ferry from Karaköy to  cross the Bosphorus on to the Asian side, as well as take the nostalgic tram which runs along Istiklal Street.  There is always something exciting happening in this area, as it encompasses Taksim Square, Istiklal Street, Galata Tower, and  Karakoy.

column3: Le Plateau has plenty to offer within walking distance. Try out Arepera or O. Noir for some of Montreal's best dining. For shopping, head to Boul- St-Laurent on Laurent Boulevard. To discover the rest of the city, take the metro at Saint-Laurent & Prince-Arthur station.  For an authentic Montreal experience, skip downtown and hang out with the locals in Le Plateau. Nestled at the foot of Mont Royal, Le Plateau is the epicenter of entertainment and culture in this diverse city. Day or night, the streets of Saint Denis, Mont Royal Ave, and Saint Laurent Boulevard come alive with residents and tourists alike. Eat your way through a variety of restaurants, and adventure through countless shops, cafés, and bars. Save some time to explore Saint Laurent Boulevard, where you'll find all sorts of unique urban art installations on every turn, thanks to the annual Montreal Mural Festival.

column3: The Kehena area is on the south east coast of Hawaii Island and encompasses several small, residential neighborhoods. Located along ‘Red Road’, named for the red cinder that used surface it, this is easily one of the most beautiful coastline routes you’ll ever drive. This area is home to Kehena black sand beach, sometimes called Dolphin Beach for the spinner dolphins that frequent it, where you can enjoy a refreshing swim or relax on the sand.   To the south, lava has been flowing for over 30 years and is often visible from the Kalapana lava viewing area, less than 10 minutes away by car. column3: Gracia used to be a separate town on the edge of Barcelona until it was absorbed by its larger neighbour. It is renowned for the fact that it has always managed to maintain an independent character from the rest of the city. The neighbourhood is richly cultural, from the diversity of people walking its streets to street parties, human towers, live music and fireworks, a wide variety of restaurants, and cinemas, theatres and galleries. The unique architecture also adds a charm of its own. The narrow streets, little squares and small buildings are reminiscent of the town it used to be, but the spectrum of restaurants, bars, shops and cinemas betray its status as a part of Barcelona, Catalunya’s capital city. Gracia offers the choice of quiet sleepy side streets alongside the life and bustle of its squares.

column3: Maui’s unique and varied terrain offers a multitude of activities. From relaxing on some of the world’s most beautiful white sand beaches to the more adventurous undertakings of zip-lining and paragliding. Kauhale Makai's location is such that there are many activities and attractions right at your finger tips. Some of Maui’s top attractions are: Maalaea Harbor - 6 miles - Many boats leave from Maalaea on snorkeling trips, deep sea fishing, scuba diving, whale watching (in season), sunset cruises, and more. It is much faster to leave from Maalaea Harbor than Lahaina Harbor when taking trips to Molokini Crater and Turtle Town. Other attractions include Maui Ocean Center, Haleakala Volcano, Shops at Wailea, Iao Valley, Wailea Golf Club, King Kamehameha Golf Club, Maui Tropical Plantation, and the Whale Sanctuary. The town of Kihei is a quant, laid-back beach town boasting some of Maui’s most pristine stretches of white sand and turquoise waters. South Maui is fun for couples and families

column3: The neighborhood is close to the center but far enough to avoid the hustle and bustle of the city. This was a typical neighborhood populated by workers of Porto that served in the hat and weaving factory. Now the factory has been transformed into an artistic foundation, the Fábrica Social - Fundação Escultor José Rodrigues (he is the author of the Ribeira cube sculpture)] that usually hosts exhibitions, laboratories and workshops. At the back of the Fábrica remains one of the most curious places of Porto ... and one of my favorites! A series of 'ruin' houses that this foundation - instead of demolishing them - gave an original approach to it when in 2010 it hosted the 'Visual Street Performance' event. This event brought together graffiters from all over the country and also from abroad to paint street art Live. The art remained there and only a few know that behind the building of master José Rodrigues' studio there are graffiti works by HBSR, Hium, Klit, Mars, Vhils, Youth One, by Po

Located approximately ten miles west of Copacabana, Barra, as the locals call their home, is a Brazilian beach neighborhood that has a decidedly American feel. If you want to meet native people go directly to barra da tijuca beach, on which tourist could be sometimes a rare treasure. Spending time at the beach and seeing what the local restaurants have to offer are just two of the options for things to do in Barra. This is also an excellent shopping destination. On a Barra da Tijuca shopping spree, you can hit the largest shopping mall in Latin America, visit any number of smaller shopping malls, and check out the goods at a variety of upscale boutiques or specialty stores. We are in Williamsburg proper here at Bedford Ave, not just a nearby subway stop to it or a far walk away. The waterfront area is the most desirable part of Williamsburg, and Bedford ave is the main street. Everything is close, and neighborhood is safe. column3: É um bairro muito bem localizado, com comércio e transporte fácil.  O apartamento fica a 10 minutos da Lagoa e do Parque Lage. Próximo ao túnel Rebouças que liga a Zona Sul a Zona Norte da cidade. O bairro faz divisa com os bairros da Lagoa, Gávea, Humaitá. A quantidade de vegetação e a proximidade com a Lagoa dão ao bairro uma temperatura mais amena que a média da cidade do Rio de Janeiro.

column3: The apartment which is in the Diamond Head Beach Hotel and Residences is uniquely located.  The  famous Kapiolani Park is just across the street. Waking distance to the Aquarium, zoo, Waikiki Beach.  A 5 minute drive or a 20 min to Diamond Head Crater and Saturday Farmers Market.  Restaurants are at you finger tips.  Michel's, Lulu's,  Tucker and Bevy, Bogart's Cafe. The Pacific Ocean is your backyard.  Relax on the lawn to watch the beautiful sunsets.   Please Note:  Check House Rules for information on taxes that  will need to be collected.
